# These strings are used in the about:robots page, which ties in with the
# robots theme used in the Firefox 3 Beta 2/3 first run pages.
# They're just meant to be fun and whimsical, with references to some geeky
# but well-known robots in movies and books. Be creative with translations!

# Nonsense line from the movie "The Day The Earth Stood Still".
# No translation needed.
robots-page-title = Gort! Klaatu barada nikto!

# Movie: Logan's Run... Box (cybog): "Welcome Humans! I am ready for you."
robots-title = Welcome Humans!

# Movie: The Day The Earth Stood Still. Spoken by Klaatu.
robots-short-desc = We have come to visit you in peace and with goodwill!

# Various books by Isaac Asimov.
# http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Laws_of_Robotics
robots-long-desc-1 =
  | Robots may not injure a human being or, through inaction, 
  | allow a human being to come to harm.

# Movie: Blade Runner. Batty: "I've seen things you people wouldn’t believe..."
robots-long-desc-2 = Robots have seen things you people wouldn’t believe.

# Book: Hitchhiker’s Guide To The Galaxy. What the Sirius Cybernetics
# Corporation calls robots.
robots-long-desc-3 = Robots are Your Plastic Pal Who’s Fun To Be With.

# TV: Futurama. Bender's first line is "Bite my shiny metal ass."
robots-long-desc-4 =
  | Robots have shiny metal posteriors which should not be bitten.

# TV: Battlestar Galactica (2004 series). From the opening text.
robots-trailer-desc = And they have a plan.


